WEBVTT

00:34.534 --> 00:36.786
Tristan!
          How've you been?

00:36.828 --> 00:38.997
You know you be
        all up in my stories.

00:39.039 --> 00:40.457
So what happened
          the other night?

00:40.498 --> 00:42.042
Told her that
          I needed a break.

00:42.083 --> 00:44.627
-Good for you.
      -You wanna go on a date?

00:44.669 --> 00:47.213
Vanessa?

00:47.255 --> 00:48.882
I'm staying with Nia
          for a little while.

00:48.923 --> 00:51.509
Welcome home, roomie!

00:51.551 --> 00:54.846
-I'm Jason.
               -Chuck.

00:54.888 --> 00:57.557
-You wanna hang out again?

00:57.599 --> 01:00.351
Why do first dates always
      feel like job interviews?

01:00.393 --> 01:01.770
I would love to kiss you.

01:13.281 --> 01:15.366
What's up?

01:15.408 --> 01:17.368
Hattie, who's this?

01:17.410 --> 01:20.580
-You must be Marie.
       -I am, and you must be?

01:20.622 --> 01:22.290
This is my
         lady friend, Idina.

01:22.332 --> 01:23.917
Don't call me that.

01:23.958 --> 01:26.294
Well, we're still working
     on what to call each other.

01:26.336 --> 01:28.463
I mean, I didn't wanna
      call you my Nubian queen,

01:28.505 --> 01:30.256
but I also didn't
      wanna call you my friend,

01:30.298 --> 01:31.424
'cause that just
        sounds disrespectful.

01:31.466 --> 01:32.926
Because, like,
         Marie's my friend,

01:32.967 --> 01:34.511
-but we're more than friends--
                -Shh.

01:34.552 --> 01:35.929
Hattie, can I talk
        to you for a second?

01:35.970 --> 01:39.390
-Oh, yeah. Yeah.

01:39.432 --> 01:41.601
-What are you doing?
               -What?

01:41.643 --> 01:43.103
You told me I should go
      to Moondance and network.

01:43.144 --> 01:44.604
That's what I'm doing.

01:44.646 --> 01:46.272
No, I said that
   I could bring a guest this year

01:46.314 --> 01:47.607
and that you should come
         because it would be

01:47.649 --> 01:49.400
a good opportunity
       for you to meet people

01:49.442 --> 01:51.027
-and talk to the other writers.
          -Mm-hmm.

01:51.069 --> 01:53.863
I also said that it could be a
   fun getaway for us as friends.

01:53.905 --> 01:57.909
Oh, you wanted quality time.

01:57.951 --> 02:00.620
-My bad, boo, I'm--
           -Don't do that.

02:00.662 --> 02:04.290
Look, this girl
   could really be the one, okay?

02:04.332 --> 02:06.167
And I really
      wanted her to go with us.

02:06.209 --> 02:08.128
Yeah, but I only gave you
       one first-class ticket.

02:08.169 --> 02:11.339
I know, that's why I traded
    it in for two coach tickets.

02:11.381 --> 02:14.134
Hey, I even had enough
     money left over for snacks.

02:14.175 --> 02:17.011
Who's ready for Moondance?

02:17.053 --> 02:18.680
I know I am!

02:18.721 --> 02:22.100
Marie, you ready to go sit
    in some dark rooms together?

02:22.142 --> 02:24.978
-Uh...
    -And watch movies, obviously.

02:25.019 --> 02:26.521
--Right.

02:26.563 --> 02:28.356
Yeah, of course!
             So excited.

02:30.233 --> 02:32.318
All right, come on, baby.

02:32.360 --> 02:35.655
upbeat hip-hop music

02:35.697 --> 02:36.990
Let's go

02:41.035 --> 02:43.121
Yeah, I know you lookin',
        know you lookin' at me

02:43.163 --> 02:45.165
Everybody talkin' 'bout
       the stuff I'm gonna see

02:45.206 --> 02:47.333
Real nice with it,
          but my attitude be

02:47.375 --> 02:49.335
Step up off your feelings
         go get to the green

02:49.377 --> 02:51.296
Money, money, money,
         money, money, money

02:51.337 --> 02:52.839
I didn't know
          you had a sister.

02:52.881 --> 02:55.133
Yeah, we were
      never really that close.

02:55.175 --> 02:58.136
Mm. Why not?

02:58.178 --> 03:00.138
We've always
         been so different.

03:00.180 --> 03:03.349
When we were growing up,
     I was into arts and crafts,

03:03.391 --> 03:05.351
and she was into boys
            and dresses.

03:05.393 --> 03:07.020
Mm.

03:07.061 --> 03:08.521
I get it.

03:08.563 --> 03:10.690
I always wanted a sibling
          growing up, man.

03:10.732 --> 03:12.692
I hated being a only child.

03:12.734 --> 03:15.528
I never had anybody to talk to.

03:15.570 --> 03:17.989
My sister used to
          talk my ear off.

03:18.031 --> 03:19.741
-Yeah?
               -Yeah.

03:19.782 --> 03:21.701
And she would always talk
      about her future husband

03:21.743 --> 03:23.870
and all the kids
        they were gonna have.

03:23.912 --> 03:26.748
I'm surprised she
    doesn't have ten kids by now.

03:26.789 --> 03:29.834
Mm. Sounds like
    your sister's big on family.

03:29.876 --> 03:31.377
I'm big on family, too,

03:31.419 --> 03:34.255
just the kind I can choose.

03:34.297 --> 03:36.424
Hey, I don't have
        much of either, so...

03:36.466 --> 03:38.968
I'm more of a lone soldier.

03:39.010 --> 03:40.887
Is that why you go
       for long bouts of time

03:40.929 --> 03:42.388
where I don't hear from you?

03:42.430 --> 03:44.515
No.

03:44.557 --> 03:47.060
That's just me checking in
            with myself.

03:47.101 --> 03:50.146
Mm. Do you have
         to do it for weeks?

03:50.188 --> 03:52.398
Sometimes.
      You don't you ever do it?

03:52.440 --> 03:54.734
No, I don't have the luxury.

03:56.277 --> 03:58.238
We all do.

03:58.279 --> 04:00.240
Just have to commit to it.

04:06.037 --> 04:08.206
I can barely get
         a moment to myself

04:08.248 --> 04:10.541
without my sister
       breathing down my neck.

04:10.583 --> 04:12.627
Yeah?

04:12.669 --> 04:14.921
Thanks for giving me
     an excuse to go for a walk.

04:14.963 --> 04:17.715
Anytime.

04:17.757 --> 04:19.550
-Wanna sit down?
               -Yeah.

04:30.728 --> 04:32.272
Who's Ben?

04:32.313 --> 04:34.399
I thought you
         didn't get jealous.

04:37.026 --> 04:39.904
Nah, I'm just curious.

04:39.946 --> 04:42.991
He works with Marie.
      He's an exec at Monument.

04:44.742 --> 04:46.953
-Cool.
            -You nervous?

04:50.248 --> 04:52.083
Maybe.

04:52.125 --> 04:54.961
smooth R&B music

04:59.173 --> 05:01.467
All right,
     so what's on your schedule?

05:01.509 --> 05:04.762
Well, I'm scheduled
   to see a lot of documentaries.

05:04.804 --> 05:07.056
One about our
     failing health care system,

05:07.098 --> 05:09.309
one about our
       failing school system,

05:09.350 --> 05:11.477
and apparently there's
   a documentary that can tell you

05:11.519 --> 05:13.479
exactly when
       the world's gonna end.

05:13.521 --> 05:15.398
I think
     that's showing at midnight.

05:15.440 --> 05:17.275
Oof. Remind me
       not to watch that one.

05:18.359 --> 05:19.861
My anxiety's already acting up.

05:21.904 --> 05:25.283
-Really?
               -What?

05:25.325 --> 05:27.827
-Ben's not coming.
              -Why not?

05:27.869 --> 05:30.163
He said something came up.

05:30.204 --> 05:31.873
That's odd.
         He loves Moondance.

05:31.914 --> 05:33.791
It's also his job
      to watch all these movies

05:33.833 --> 05:35.043
so I don't have to.

05:35.084 --> 05:37.378
I can do that for you.

05:39.756 --> 05:42.175
Thank you.

05:42.216 --> 05:44.969
Look, I just really
    wanna buy a movie this year.

05:45.011 --> 05:46.971
Well, then we have
       to be more aggressive.

05:47.013 --> 05:48.598
We can't break the bank.

05:48.639 --> 05:50.266
Every year,
         we come down here,

05:50.308 --> 05:52.477
we watch a bunch of movies,
     and we never buy anything.

05:52.518 --> 05:53.936
And this year
       I want to change that.

05:53.978 --> 05:55.688
Okay.

05:55.730 --> 05:58.024
Just try and find me
      something we can afford.

05:58.066 --> 06:01.402
-I will do my best.
          -I know you will.

06:03.404 --> 06:07.617
It's probably just like
     barn-like on the outside...

06:07.658 --> 06:10.244
Nah, this can't be it.

06:13.247 --> 06:15.375
What the hell?

06:17.043 --> 06:19.545
This ain't what
       it looked like online.

06:19.587 --> 06:24.258
Hattie, you didn't look
    into this before we got here?

06:24.300 --> 06:26.886
Come on, we can make it work.

06:26.928 --> 06:28.888
You-you wanna go get
             some pizza?

06:28.930 --> 06:31.140
Yeah, let's just settle in...

06:31.182 --> 06:33.184
Yeah...

06:33.226 --> 06:36.062
can we go see
         some movies first?

06:36.104 --> 06:38.856
Yeah, let me just figure out
        the ticket situation.

06:38.898 --> 06:41.317
You don't already have that
            figured out?

06:41.359 --> 06:43.903
Look, turning this trip
        into a couple's thing

06:43.945 --> 06:46.739
was spur of the moment, okay?

06:46.781 --> 06:48.616
That's obvious.

06:48.658 --> 06:50.076
Why you have to do it
             like that?

06:50.118 --> 06:52.161
Why is this our bed?

06:52.203 --> 06:55.164
-What do you want me to do?
       -Plan ahead next time.

06:55.206 --> 06:56.833
Look, you're the one
          that was talking

06:56.874 --> 06:59.043
about how you wanted to go
       to Moondance so badly.

06:59.085 --> 07:00.920
And now you here,
           under the moon,

07:00.962 --> 07:02.255
and I'm ready to dance,

07:02.296 --> 07:03.756
and you pouting

07:03.798 --> 07:06.592
'cause I ain't got
     everything figured out yet.

07:06.634 --> 07:08.719
You're right.

07:08.761 --> 07:10.263
Sorry.

07:10.304 --> 07:12.432
I'm just super organized,

07:12.473 --> 07:16.936
and I get freaked out
   when everything isn't in order.

07:16.978 --> 07:20.398
Look, I'm sorry I don't have
    my shit together, all right?

07:20.440 --> 07:22.942
I was just so excited
        about us coming here

07:22.984 --> 07:26.112
that I didn't think
         everything through.

07:26.154 --> 07:28.114
It's okay.

07:28.156 --> 07:30.616
Film festivals aren't about
     hanging out in your hotel.

07:30.658 --> 07:32.118
It's about being out and about.

07:32.160 --> 07:33.453
-Mm-hmm.
            -So let's go.

07:33.494 --> 07:36.414
-Yeah, let's go.
              -Mm-hmm.

07:36.456 --> 07:39.041
Mm.
   Yes, let's get up out of here.

07:39.083 --> 07:41.002
-Please.
       -Oh, put your stuff up,

07:41.043 --> 07:42.545
just in case there's
        some roaches in here.

07:42.587 --> 07:44.130
Don't you say that.
   See, now I'm gonna be paranoid.

07:44.172 --> 07:45.756
No, they don't have roaches,
        but I'm just saying--

07:45.798 --> 07:47.633
Now I'm gonna be feelin'
      like they crawling on me!

07:47.675 --> 07:49.260
-We about to go get--
              -Hold up.

07:49.302 --> 07:51.095
No, no, no, that was nothing.
              Come on.

07:51.137 --> 07:53.264
-You ju--That's a roach!
        -That's not a roach!

07:53.306 --> 07:55.766
-Oh, my God, Hattie!
      -It's a water bug! Stop!

07:55.808 --> 07:59.061
You don't know the difference
   between roaches and water bugs?

07:59.103 --> 08:01.814
-Need any help?
       -No, I think I got it.

08:01.856 --> 08:03.900
Come on, hand it to me.

08:03.941 --> 08:06.569
-Okay, thank you.
          -You're welcome.

08:06.611 --> 08:08.821
Gosh, why do they give us
      so much shit every year?

08:08.863 --> 08:10.490
It's such a waste.

08:10.531 --> 08:13.117
I always give it to my family.
     They get a kick out of it.

08:13.159 --> 08:16.746
Wow. My family doesn't get
       excited about anything.

08:16.787 --> 08:18.289
They're all so jaded.

08:18.331 --> 08:21.167
-Do you still get excited?

08:21.209 --> 08:23.294
It's not the festival
        that gets me excited.

08:23.336 --> 08:25.713
It's the people.

08:28.299 --> 08:30.635
So, uh, you see anything good?

08:30.676 --> 08:34.222
Yeah, "Tears of Gila River."

08:34.263 --> 08:36.265
It deals with
    the intergenerational trauma

08:36.307 --> 08:38.351
of Japanese American
             internment.

08:38.392 --> 08:42.480
It's all a tragic metaphor,
    and it's so beautifully shot.

08:42.522 --> 08:44.148
Alicia Ishizuka
       wrote and directed it.

08:44.190 --> 08:46.275
-She's brilliant.
                -Wow.

08:46.317 --> 08:48.194
We should get a meeting
              with her.

08:48.236 --> 08:49.612
Already set.

08:49.654 --> 08:51.781
I'm meeting with her
       when we get back to LA.

08:51.822 --> 08:53.533
Great.

08:55.201 --> 08:57.828
Um...

08:57.870 --> 09:00.414
-so I'll see you at dinner.

09:00.456 --> 09:03.584
-Yeah, I look forward to it.
              -Me too.

09:03.626 --> 09:05.670
Nice room.

09:05.711 --> 09:08.256
It better be.

09:08.297 --> 09:10.216
All right, see you later.

09:16.597 --> 09:19.725
mellow music

09:51.257 --> 09:53.301
upbeat jazz music

09:57.430 --> 09:59.223
Hey!

09:59.265 --> 10:02.018
Um, you can try waiting
      in the "no ticket" line.

10:02.059 --> 10:04.520
Oh, that sounds a little
      bit like flying stand-by.

10:04.562 --> 10:06.105
That's exactly
           what it's like.

10:06.147 --> 10:07.773
You have to hope and pray
       the theater isn't full.

10:07.815 --> 10:09.609
How often does it fill up?

10:09.650 --> 10:12.862
Oh, I'd say about 99% of
   the time, they're pretty full.

10:12.903 --> 10:15.698
Well, would you
    have any suggestions for us?

10:15.740 --> 10:17.450
Hang out
         outside the theater

10:17.491 --> 10:19.619
and see if there
       are any extra tickets.

10:19.660 --> 10:21.871
Anything else?

10:21.912 --> 10:23.956
Do you have any friends
          with VIP passes?

10:23.998 --> 10:27.293
Yes uh, my friend is here.
    She works for a major studio.

10:27.335 --> 10:28.961
Well, she can bring
          a buddy with her.

10:29.003 --> 10:30.796
-Dope!
           -But just one.

10:30.838 --> 10:32.465
That's how
       the buddy system works.

10:35.635 --> 10:38.429
We can just trade off.

10:38.471 --> 10:40.723
Well, I was hoping we could
      watch the movies together

10:40.765 --> 10:42.141
and then talk
        about 'em afterwards.

10:42.183 --> 10:44.393
Oh, that's so sweet.

10:44.435 --> 10:47.605
Sweet enough for you to hook
    us up with some tickets, fam?

10:47.647 --> 10:50.483
Not even if you promised
         me your firstborn.

10:50.524 --> 10:53.861
Damn, y'all take
         this shit serious.

10:53.903 --> 10:55.488
It's not just a festival.

10:55.529 --> 10:58.115
It's a group of people
    very dedicated to making sure

10:58.157 --> 11:00.534
indie cinema doesn't die,
          but also a place

11:00.576 --> 11:02.370
for rich
     Hollywood films to thrive.

11:02.411 --> 11:05.164
We like to be
         fair and balanced.

11:05.206 --> 11:07.124
-You like to be fair?
     -And balanced!

11:07.166 --> 11:08.709
Come on, fam, I thought

11:08.751 --> 11:10.503
-you was gonna be cool.
               -Right.

11:10.544 --> 11:14.048
Wow, right.
     I thought you was an ally!

11:17.218 --> 11:18.844
So let's move on to the team

11:18.886 --> 11:20.513
from Monument Pictures.

11:20.554 --> 11:22.848
Marie Owens,
         Creative Executive

11:22.890 --> 11:24.183
at Monument Pictures.

11:24.225 --> 11:27.061
Hey, I'm Zach Leob,
      President of Production.

11:27.103 --> 11:29.563
I'm here standing in
      for one of my colleagues,

11:29.605 --> 11:31.857
Ben Okwu, who unfortunately
          couldn't make it.

11:31.899 --> 11:33.359
And right off the bat,
          I just wanna take

11:33.401 --> 11:36.195
this opportunity to apologize
          for my whiteness.

11:38.030 --> 11:39.532
You don't have to
         apologize for that.

11:39.573 --> 11:41.867
Just make sure you
        don't talk too much.

11:41.909 --> 11:43.369
What, he be talkin--

11:43.411 --> 11:44.995
Does anyone have
           any questions?

11:45.037 --> 11:47.832
Oh, I got--um, you will not
     be centered at this event.

11:47.873 --> 11:49.500
Can you...

11:49.542 --> 11:52.002
Give me a foot.
             Thank you.

11:52.044 --> 11:54.046
Hey, best friend.

11:54.088 --> 11:55.965
I just had a quick question.

11:56.006 --> 11:59.093
What type of films
      are y'all trying to buy?

11:59.135 --> 12:01.929
-Profitable films--
           -Great films--

12:01.971 --> 12:03.597
Well, which one is it?

12:03.639 --> 12:06.559
Because I think that you know
    profitable is--I'm not done!

12:06.600 --> 12:08.894
There's just one question
             per person.

12:08.936 --> 12:10.563
-I'm not done.
                -Ah.

12:10.604 --> 12:12.064
Thank you.

12:12.106 --> 12:13.941
You better be glad
     I ain't tryin' to show out.

12:13.983 --> 12:16.193
-Thank you.
           -What?

12:16.235 --> 12:19.238
To be honest, we don't know
       what we're looking for.

12:19.280 --> 12:21.365
Finding a great movie

12:21.407 --> 12:23.576
or discovering
        an amazing filmmaker

12:23.617 --> 12:26.036
is kind of like falling
              in love.

12:26.078 --> 12:28.247
When you know, you know.

12:28.289 --> 12:31.667
And sometimes you don't,
     so you go into development,

12:31.709 --> 12:33.377
and you hope
          to find something

12:33.419 --> 12:35.921
that you can all agree on,
             hopefully.

12:35.963 --> 12:37.423
It's all case by case.

12:37.465 --> 12:40.050
So don't try to bring us
    something you think we want.

12:40.092 --> 12:42.261
Bring us a great idea.

12:42.303 --> 12:45.097
Zach, would you
         like to elaborate?

12:45.139 --> 12:49.268
No, I agree with everything
          Marie just said.

12:49.310 --> 12:51.937
And being inclusive
     is great for business, too.

12:51.979 --> 12:53.856
Absolutely.

12:53.898 --> 12:55.941
It's estimated
      that the American economy

12:55.983 --> 12:58.569
has lost over $16 trillion

12:58.611 --> 13:01.781
over the last 20 years
           due to racism.

13:01.822 --> 13:05.117
By including everyone, not only
   do we improve our bottom line,

13:05.159 --> 13:07.661
but we also get to be
    on the right side of history.

13:10.998 --> 13:13.959
upbeat music

13:19.507 --> 13:22.635
-Where are all my crystals?
          -I cleaned them.

13:22.676 --> 13:25.638
I don't need you
        to clean my crystals!

13:25.679 --> 13:27.139
They were a little dusty.

13:27.181 --> 13:28.933
Can you put them back
        where you found them

13:28.974 --> 13:31.477
and never touch them again,
               please?

13:45.699 --> 13:48.619
Hey, what are you doing?

13:48.661 --> 13:50.579
Trying to not to
           kill my sister.

13:50.621 --> 13:53.499
Really?

13:53.541 --> 13:55.835
-How's the festival?
     -I don't know. I didn't go.

13:55.876 --> 13:57.419
Why not?

13:57.461 --> 13:59.588
I'm sick
       of working at Monument.

13:59.630 --> 14:01.841
-What do you mean?
       -I can't be free there.

14:01.882 --> 14:03.008
Every time I pitch something,

14:03.050 --> 14:04.927
I just get--
        I just get shot down.

14:04.969 --> 14:06.637
But you have to keep trying.

14:06.679 --> 14:08.848
I'm thinking
     of striking out on my own.

14:08.889 --> 14:11.016
That sounds risky.

14:11.058 --> 14:12.852
Look, I'm tired
      of asking for permission.

14:12.893 --> 14:16.063
I-I know what the people want.

14:16.105 --> 14:19.316
I just need the right team
    behind me to make it happen.

14:19.358 --> 14:22.862
If I--if I went out on my own,
    would you--would you help me?

14:22.903 --> 14:25.197
I'm still tryin'
       to build my own career.

14:25.239 --> 14:27.533
We could build
        our careers together.

14:27.575 --> 14:29.201
I don't know.

14:29.243 --> 14:31.787
No, I-I believe in you.

14:31.829 --> 14:33.622
I believe in you, too.

14:33.664 --> 14:35.958
So what do you say?

14:36.000 --> 14:39.003
smooth music

14:39.044 --> 14:42.214
You don't have
    to make a decision right now.

14:42.256 --> 14:44.174
Just chew on it.

14:44.216 --> 14:48.387
-Okay, I will.
             -Okay, bye.

15:02.776 --> 15:05.237
Is it just me, or did
   that movie not make any sense?

15:05.279 --> 15:07.656
I think it was supposed
      to be one long metaphor.

15:07.698 --> 15:10.200
-But for what?
          -Human existence.

15:10.242 --> 15:11.243
What?

15:11.285 --> 15:12.661
That don't make any sense.

15:12.703 --> 15:14.371
I kind of liked it.

15:14.413 --> 15:16.081
You were falling asleep.
              Stop it.

15:16.123 --> 15:17.541
Because we've been walking
           around all day

15:17.583 --> 15:19.251
trying to get into a movie.

15:19.293 --> 15:21.754
Yeah, well, we finally got
     into one, and it was awful.

15:21.795 --> 15:24.298
I'm just glad we finally
        got to see something.

15:24.340 --> 15:25.925
Yeah, me too.

15:25.966 --> 15:28.802
I just hate that it was
       so long and confusing.

15:28.844 --> 15:31.305
Ooh, Chalet Chic.

15:31.347 --> 15:33.015
You wanna go to a party
              tonight?

15:33.057 --> 15:34.475
How are we supposed to get in?

15:34.516 --> 15:36.936
You with me!
    I'm gonna charm the bouncer.

15:36.977 --> 15:40.147
I'll teach you to flamenco.
       I learned it in Spain.

15:40.189 --> 15:41.815
Nah, I'm lyin'.
    I ain't never been to Spain.

15:41.857 --> 15:43.901
But I can still teach you.
              Come on!

15:43.943 --> 15:48.072
For the last time,
       my name is Marie Owens,

15:48.113 --> 15:50.616
and I work
       for Monument Pictures.

15:50.658 --> 15:53.202
-Marie Owens?
          -Yeah, that's me!

15:53.243 --> 15:54.870
Oh, yeah, yeah,
        she's already inside.

15:54.912 --> 15:57.373
-Come on, move aside.
        -Ain't that a bitch.

15:57.414 --> 16:00.793
I think she's still mad
       you ditched her for me.

16:00.834 --> 16:03.128
She could at least text me
   and tell me where she's going.

16:03.170 --> 16:06.048
She got us into that inclusion
    and diversity panel earlier.

16:06.090 --> 16:08.634
'Cause ain't nobody
          wanna go to that!

16:08.676 --> 16:10.260
Hattie?

16:10.302 --> 16:12.721
What's up?
           How you doin'?

16:12.763 --> 16:15.766
I'm good.
   I got a movie in the festival.

16:15.808 --> 16:17.226
Dope!

16:17.267 --> 16:19.395
Um, Alicia,
       this is my girl, Idina.

16:19.436 --> 16:20.980
Idina, this is Alicia.

16:21.021 --> 16:24.483
We met at a screening
    of Alicia's movie last year.

16:24.525 --> 16:26.318
It was way better
       than what we just saw.

16:26.360 --> 16:28.445
-What'd you guys just see?
        -"Life is a Mystery."

16:28.487 --> 16:30.364
Oh, man,
   I heard that one was brilliant.

16:30.406 --> 16:32.116
Hattie hated it.

16:32.157 --> 16:33.742
Well, I didn't hate it.

16:33.784 --> 16:36.495
I just think I should watch
       it a couple more times.

16:36.537 --> 16:38.539
Mm, don't try to act
        like you like it now.

16:40.249 --> 16:41.667
Hattie,
      what are you working on?

16:41.709 --> 16:45.254
Uh, well, I been working
       on this pilot recently.

16:45.295 --> 16:46.630
It's pretty good, too.

16:46.672 --> 16:48.340
Well, if you want,
       you can send it to me,

16:48.382 --> 16:49.967
and I can ask my manager
             to read it.

16:50.009 --> 16:51.176
Are you serious?

16:51.218 --> 16:52.845
Sure, he's young and hungry.

16:52.886 --> 16:55.055
I think he might like you.

16:55.097 --> 16:56.974
Bet.

16:57.016 --> 16:59.018
I mean, I'll send
       you that shit tonight.

16:59.059 --> 17:00.936
I'll check it
          for typos first.

17:00.978 --> 17:04.356
Yeah, she's always making sure
   I don't spell restaurant wrong.

17:04.398 --> 17:05.941
-I hate that word.
             -A then U.

17:05.983 --> 17:07.359
Yeah, it's tricky!

17:07.401 --> 17:11.488
That and "embarrassment"--
       it gets me every time.

17:11.530 --> 17:13.490
Well, you have
        a good night, ladies.

17:13.532 --> 17:15.284
You too.

17:16.535 --> 17:17.828
What?

17:17.870 --> 17:19.496
I don't know
       if your script is ready

17:19.538 --> 17:21.707
to send to managers yet.

17:21.749 --> 17:24.543
She said that he's young
        and hungry, so am I.

17:24.585 --> 17:26.962
-So...

17:27.004 --> 17:28.714
Look, I need
        you to believe in me.

17:28.756 --> 17:31.425
-I do.
         -Then act like it.

17:33.635 --> 17:35.429
Whoa, whoa, nice try.
         Come on, let's go.

17:35.471 --> 17:36.805
Come on, man, we right here!

17:36.847 --> 17:38.182
Yeah, yeah,
   now we're gonna be out there.

17:38.223 --> 17:39.641
-Let's go.
          -All right, man.

17:39.683 --> 17:41.060
-Come on, let's go.
             -Psych! Ha!

17:41.101 --> 17:42.686
-Yeah.
        -Oh, you got scared.

17:42.728 --> 17:44.688
That was funny. That was funny.
     Let's go be funny outside.

17:44.730 --> 17:46.440
What happened to
     Black and brown relations?

17:46.482 --> 17:48.984
-Oh, it's beautiful.
            -Oh, my gosh.

17:49.026 --> 17:51.070
Hope y'all don't get in.

17:51.111 --> 17:54.031
smooth music

18:03.248 --> 18:05.626
I think your script
      needs a few more passes.

18:07.419 --> 18:10.172
Look, this is the opportunity
        of a lifetime, okay?

18:10.214 --> 18:12.257
I'm not about to miss this.

18:12.299 --> 18:15.094
No one's gonna remember
   when you sent them your script.

18:15.135 --> 18:17.721
They're just gonna remember
       how it made them feel.

18:17.763 --> 18:19.598
Why don't you wait
            until you get

18:19.640 --> 18:21.225
the next round
      of notes from the group,

18:21.266 --> 18:24.269
do another pass,
      and then send it to her?

18:24.311 --> 18:26.271
Why you hating on my dream?

18:26.313 --> 18:28.899
I'm just trying to make sure
    you don't send her something

18:28.941 --> 18:31.610
before it's ready.

18:31.652 --> 18:34.655
First impressions
          last a long time.

18:34.696 --> 18:37.616
Didn't you say that my script
         had gotten better?

18:37.658 --> 18:41.578
It is!
      It's just not there yet.

18:41.620 --> 18:43.163
Well, how would you know?

18:43.205 --> 18:45.582
You still making latte art
          at a coffee shop.

18:50.879 --> 18:52.589
You know what I mean.

18:54.216 --> 18:57.219
Look, I'm just trying
            to help you.

18:57.261 --> 18:59.096
Well, look,
       I don't need your help.

18:59.138 --> 19:01.223
I need your support,
           and I need you

19:01.265 --> 19:03.475
to go over this email
        before I send it out.

19:05.853 --> 19:07.980
You spelled "sincerely" wrong.

19:09.648 --> 19:11.233
See?

19:11.275 --> 19:12.985
What would I do without you?

19:13.026 --> 19:14.570
Use spell check?

19:25.372 --> 19:28.500
You're too cute to eat.

19:37.301 --> 19:40.053
Is it just me, babe,
       or does your hotel room

19:40.095 --> 19:41.513
look a lot like
            your apartment?

19:41.555 --> 19:46.310
Oh, yeah, I, uh--I meant
     to tell you, I-I didn't go.

19:46.351 --> 19:47.936
Why?

19:47.978 --> 19:50.355
Wait, so you've been in LA
          this whole time?

19:50.397 --> 19:52.357
I didn't--didn't
       really wanna get into it.

19:52.399 --> 19:53.775
What's going on?

19:53.817 --> 19:56.403
Just, uh, work.

19:56.445 --> 19:58.155
Why are you being so weird?

19:59.990 --> 20:01.575
Uh...

20:03.285 --> 20:05.495
I-I think
       we should take a break.

20:05.537 --> 20:07.497
I knew this was coming.

20:07.539 --> 20:11.084
-Is it because I'm white?
       -Of course not, no, no.

20:11.126 --> 20:15.714
I just--I just think
   we've gone as far as we can go.

20:15.756 --> 20:17.299
Says who, you?

20:17.341 --> 20:18.550
We haven't been
            the same since--

20:18.592 --> 20:19.968
Your promotion.

20:20.010 --> 20:22.054
It's not that,
     I'm just growing, you know?

20:22.095 --> 20:25.265
-And I'm not?
     -Not at the same rate, no.

20:28.101 --> 20:30.145
I can't believe you're doing
         this over FaceTime.

20:30.187 --> 20:32.231
I know, I just don't want
      to feel like an asshole.

20:32.272 --> 20:33.899
Ben, whether
         you like it or not,

20:33.941 --> 20:35.651
you're always gonna
       feel like an asshole...

20:35.692 --> 20:37.069
-because you are one.

20:45.869 --> 20:47.079
I'm sorry.

20:57.631 --> 21:00.592
Man, it's so beautiful.

21:00.634 --> 21:02.302
I know.

21:02.344 --> 21:05.597
I always appreciate the scenery
        more than the cinema.

21:05.639 --> 21:07.724
Must you be so tough
           on everything?

21:07.766 --> 21:09.935
-I'm not that tough.
           -Yes, you are.

21:09.977 --> 21:12.896
You give me shit,
        and I run the studio.

21:12.938 --> 21:16.942
I have high standards.
           I always have.

21:16.984 --> 21:19.444
Yeah,
   they're hard to meet sometimes.

21:19.486 --> 21:22.364
-Should I apologize for that?
          -No, not at all.

21:22.406 --> 21:24.199
I like it.

21:24.241 --> 21:26.451
I know you do.

21:26.493 --> 21:28.287
Well, I'm not tired.

21:30.038 --> 21:31.915
Neither am I.

21:31.957 --> 21:35.544
Should we, uh...
         go get a night cap?

21:37.004 --> 21:40.048
I don't know
       if that's a good idea.

21:42.509 --> 21:44.594
Yeah, you're right.

21:44.636 --> 21:47.806
It's been a long day.
         We should turn in.

21:47.848 --> 21:51.143
Lookin' fine as hell
          in this moonlight

21:51.184 --> 21:54.479
Ooh, in the mornin'
        you gonna hate me like

21:54.521 --> 21:57.816
Damn, this bitch is crazy,
          got me playin'...

22:01.361 --> 22:03.822
Good night, Marie.

22:03.864 --> 22:05.198
Good night.

22:27.763 --> 22:30.724
mellow R&B

22:35.729 --> 22:38.440
I'm 'bout to go slow

22:38.482 --> 22:41.109
You might just go
              loco loco

22:41.151 --> 22:43.862
I know how you toy

22:43.904 --> 22:46.615
I been down
           a roller coaster

22:46.656 --> 22:49.534
Different story every day

22:49.576 --> 22:53.538
Let's give them
           somethin' to say

22:55.248 --> 22:57.876
Meet me in my room

23:00.921 --> 23:03.882
Let's start
           some more rumors

23:06.051 --> 23:09.388
Meet me in my room

23:09.429 --> 23:11.556
My room

23:11.598 --> 23:14.434
Let's start
